snippet.textDisplay:
I've been watching a lot of tutorials and have made some with ties. They're cute and all of that but OMG! These are the fastest, easiest things to make in about 20 seconds! We have bandanas just because my husband is a cowboy, but any piece of fabric about 22x21 will work. You don't even need to hem it - just folding in the edges will take care of the edges. If you don't sew, you mostly likely won't have fabric sitting around. But, if you go to WalMart or any fabric store, you can buy what's called a fat quarter which is about the same size. They're usually about
$1.75 each but you can get them on sale, too.

snippet.textDisplay:
Thanks for this video. My daughter and I have been making and donating face masks without keeping any for ourselves. Since our supplies have been exhausted, we are thankful to get any&all ideas for making face masks for our personal use. We had five bandana's laying around, and we just finished making them into masks--we used ponytail hair ties instead of rubberbands and also added a breadtie (as we are out of pipe cleaners) to use to form to fit our nose.


And again, we say thank you. Stay safe and healthy :) and best wishes to all ;)
snippet.textOriginal:
